enhanced_by.reason: addAll method internally uses the add(E, int) method to add each element from the collection.
containsAll method can be used to verify the state of the bag after elements have been added by addAll.
removeAll method can be used to revert the state of the bag after elements have been added by addAll, useful for cleanup in test cases.
retainAll method can be used to filter the bag to retain only the elements added by addAll, useful for state verification in test cases.
